summary:
I have always asked myself “how” and “why” and I have recognized that Earth Sciences are a way for better understanding and predicting how our world works. This has lead me to graduate in Geology and further my knowledge by undertakinig an MSc in Integrated Petroleum Geoscience at The University of Aberdeen. 

I have had the opportunity of living in different countries and experiencing a number of new cultures and learning environments, continuously developing love for nature and wonder for the natural power of our world. I have significant field and laboratory experience; internship at ENI UK.  Specific skills include: multi-lingual (English, Italian, French); competent using Microsoft Office Programs Matlab, mySQL, ArcGis, Origin and Mercury, team-worker and creative. 

When I'm not working, I like to explore nature and challenge myself by taking on hikes. I also enjoy painting while having a good cup of coffee.
